matthew-dean,"The fact that the fish special cannot be PROVEN to not exist does not matter. Refusing to say yes or no based on current available data is not MORE useful than returning boolean true / false. No scientist says that they can't reach a conclusion since it's technically true that cause and effect can never be proven, or it's possible that the entire world is a simulation in the scientist's mind, therefore they should assert nothing. It's technically TRUE, but that doesn't mean that technical trueness is always deterministic as to what information is USEFUL, or if those technically true things are really all that relevant.",FALSE,FALSE,106,31,74,7,FALSE,TRUE,TRUE,TRUE,0,32
