bjouhier,"In our application we use fs.existsSync (and fs.exists too BTW) in situations where 1) we are guaranteed by design to have full access on the files (simply because they are inside a directory which is completely controlled by our application) and 2) we are safe by design from race conditions (in some cases because files will not get deleted anyway, in others because concurrent operations each work with their own sandbox of files, ...) For all these scenarios the simple API does the job and it has the advantage of stating explicitly what it does (which is unambiguous because the edge cases are irrelevant).",FALSE,FALSE,104,36,89,1,FALSE,TRUE,FALSE,TRUE,0,37
bjouhier,"I think that a large part of the disagreement comes from a difference of perspective between library developers and application developers:",FALSE,FALSE,21,36,90,2,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,TRUE,0,37
